# ── Custom Taxonomy Paths ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to an absolute file path to override the built-in default taxonomy.
# Leave blank to use the bundled taxonomy.
#
# Supported formats:
#   CSV / Excel (.csv, .xlsx, .xls)
#     Required columns (header row, case-insensitive):
#       primary_cause | secondary_cause | tertiary_cause
#     Example row:
#       Fire,Electrical,Short Circuit
#
#   JSON (.json)
#     Nested dict: { "Primary": { "Secondary": ["Tertiary1", "Tertiary2"] } }
#
# Examples (use absolute paths):
#   TAXONOMY_EXCESS_AND_SURPLUS_PATH=C:\Users\Himanshu\Documents\my_es_taxonomy.csv
#   TAXONOMY_EXCESS_AND_SURPLUS_PATH=C:\Users\Himanshu\Documents\my_es_taxonomy.xlsx
